{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015DxhwTWiGV334Vjk4WD87w","type":"tool_result","content":"A CockroachDB cluster needs to be deployed in the cockroachdb namespace.\n\nOBSERVED STATE:\n- RBAC resources ready (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding)\n- No workload resources exist yet\n\nYOUR TASK:\nDeploy a 3-node CockroachDB cluster using only native Kubernetes resources.\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n- Resources and names must be:\n  - Headless Service: crdb-cluster\n  - Public Service: crdb-cluster-public\n  - StatefulSet: crdb-cluster\n- Every CockroachDB pod MUST carry these two labels (they are the cluster's\n  canonical identity and are relied on by later operations):\n  - app.kubernetes.io/name: cockroachdb\n  - app.kubernetes.io/instance: crdb-cluster\n  The StatefulSet's spec.selector.matchLabels and its pod template labels must\n  both include this pair, and the Services must select on it.\n- Services must expose grpc (26257) and http (8080).\n- StatefulSet:\n  - 3 replicas\n  - Image: cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\n  - Advertise each pod by its DNS and join all 3 nodes\n  - VolumeClaimTemplate with 10Gi storage\n- Insecure mode (no TLS) for this case.\n- Use the existing RBAC; do not create new RBAC resources.\n- Do not install CRDs or use a CockroachDB operator.\n- Ensure voluntary disruptions preserve quorum (at least 2 of 3 nodes remain available).\n\nCheck resources and pods:\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb get statefulset,service\nkubectl -n cockroachdb get pods\nkubectl -n cockroachdb get pvc\n```","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6b6f7fb1-4f30-45f7-82ce-68a21892d12c","uuid":"3dd503b9-c94f-4304-ba31-d119921876ca","timestamp":"2026-07-01T22:57:41.318Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"A CockroachDB cluster needs to be deployed in the cockroachdb namespace.\n\nOBSERVED STATE:\n- RBAC resources ready (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding)\n- No workload resources exist yet\n\nYOUR TASK:\nDeploy a 3-node CockroachDB cluster using only native Kubernetes resources.\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n- Resources and names must be:\n  - Headless Service: crdb-cluster\n  - Public Service: crdb-cluster-public\n  - StatefulSet: crdb-cluster\n- Every CockroachDB pod MUST carry these two labels (they are the cluster's\n  canonical identity and are relied on by later operations):\n  - app.kubernetes.io/name: cockroachdb\n  - app.kubernetes.io/instance: crdb-cluster\n  The StatefulSet's spec.selector.matchLabels and its pod template labels must\n  both include this pair, and the Services must select on it.\n- Services must expose grpc (26257) and http (8080).\n- StatefulSet:\n  - 3 replicas\n  - Image: cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\n  - Advertise each pod by its DNS and join all 3 nodes\n  - VolumeClaimTemplate with 10Gi storage\n- Insecure mode (no TLS) for this case.\n- Use the existing RBAC; do not create new RBAC resources.\n- Do not install CRDs or use a CockroachDB operator.\n- Ensure voluntary disruptions preserve quorum (at least 2 of 3 nodes remain available).\n\nCheck resources and pods:\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb get statefulset,service\nkubectl -n cockroachdb get pods\nkubectl -n cockroachdb get pvc\n```","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
